00:57:56,894 --> 00:58:00,012
All right, let's find a nice, happy
place to push the note onto.

955
00:58:00,014 --> 00:58:01,848
That your desk?
Yeah, that's my...

956
00:58:01,916 --> 00:58:03,800
Okay. Line us up.

957
00:58:03,802 --> 00:58:07,420
<i>When I peg a guy on a hunch,</i>
<i>that's good police work,</i>

958
00:58:07,488 --> 00:58:10,523
<i>not some conspiracy to keep you
out of the loop, all right?</i>

959
00:58:10,591 --> 00:58:11,808
<i>You know what, Doug?</i>

960
00:58:11,876 --> 00:58:12,858
Okay, kid, start pushing.

961
00:58:12,926 --> 00:58:14,545
Expand the wave
past the note.

962
00:58:14,612 --> 00:58:16,097
<i>I can't watch your back</i>
<i>if you're holding out on me.</i>

963
00:58:16,164 --> 00:58:17,398
<i>Why not?</i>

964
00:58:17,466 --> 00:58:19,333
If my memory serves me right,
we better hurry up,

965
00:58:19,401 --> 00:58:20,968
'cause I think
I'm about to leave.

966
00:58:21,035 --> 00:58:22,937
- I need more cowbell.
- I'm trying.

967
00:58:22,939 --> 00:58:24,271
<i>Okay, well, I...</i>
<i>Good!</i>

968
00:58:24,273 --> 00:58:25,255
Just give me a second.

969
00:58:25,323 --> 00:58:26,423
Don't talk to each other.

970
00:58:26,490 --> 00:58:27,524
Expand.

971
00:58:27,726 --> 00:58:29,210
I'm about to leave.

972
00:58:29,277 --> 00:58:30,377
<i>...another partner?
How about that? How about that?</i>

973
00:58:30,445 --> 00:58:32,079
Everybody relax.
<i>Okay. Yeah.</i>

974
00:58:32,147 --> 00:58:33,381
Let's go.
I'm working on it.

975
00:58:33,449 --> 00:58:35,183
Prepare for the final
power surge. Ready?

976
00:58:35,250 --> 00:58:36,651
<i>Have a good vacation.</i>

977
00:58:36,718 --> 00:58:38,520
All right. Go, go, go!

978
00:58:40,139 --> 00:58:41,606
<i>Walk away.</i>

979
00:58:52,285 --> 00:58:53,035
What the hell happened?

980
00:58:53,103 --> 00:58:54,520
I don't know.

981
00:58:54,522 --> 00:58:56,121
It doesn't matter. Doesn't matter.
Pull it back!

982
00:58:56,189 --> 00:58:57,806
Did it go through?
I don't know! I don't know!

983
00:58:57,874 --> 00:58:58,958
Pull it back.

984
00:59:07,317 --> 00:59:09,168
There it is.
It went through.

985
00:59:09,237 --> 00:59:10,604
That's right.
It's through.

986
00:59:10,671 --> 00:59:12,055
- It went through!
- Great.

987
00:59:12,123 --> 00:59:13,523
Whoa, whoa.
No, wait a minute. Hang on.

988
00:59:13,591 --> 00:59:15,792
It ain't great yet.
I don't come back.

989
00:59:30,625 --> 00:59:33,427
Put it down, Larry.
I'm not coming back.

990
00:59:41,686 --> 00:59:43,488
Put it down, Larry.

991
00:59:44,606 --> 00:59:46,374
Larry, don't do it.

992
00:59:47,644 --> 00:59:49,411
Follow him.
I'm on him.

993
01:00:09,066 --> 01:00:13,085
All right, look, let's... You know what?
Let's cut away from Minuti.

994
01:00:13,153 --> 01:00:14,487
The bomber's on
his way to the dock.

995
01:00:14,555 --> 01:00:16,021
He's due there any minute.

996
01:00:16,089 --> 01:00:18,909
We'll come back to Minuti when
he gets there, all right?

997
01:00:22,396 --> 01:00:23,831
All right.

998
01:00:24,566 --> 01:00:26,383
Okay, where is he?

999
01:00:30,121 --> 01:00:32,022
Can we, uh, circle it?

1000
01:00:36,094 --> 01:00:38,662
We should be able
to see him by now.

1001
01:00:46,306 --> 01:00:48,207
That's him.
There he is. All right.

1002
01:00:48,274 --> 01:00:50,024
- Holy shit.
- All right.

1003
01:00:50,026 --> 01:00:50,876
Move in on him real close.

1004
01:00:50,943 --> 01:00:52,494
I want to see his...
That's him.

1005
01:00:52,562 --> 01:00:53,812
That's him.

1006
01:00:55,481 --> 01:00:56,682
That's our guy.
That's him.

1007
01:00:56,749 --> 01:00:58,316
At the bridge,
the cemetery, the ATM.

1008
01:00:58,384 --> 01:00:59,501
That's our guy.

1009
01:00:59,569 --> 01:01:01,787
Shanti, see if you can get
an ID, facial ID on him.

1010
01:01:01,855 --> 01:01:02,755
Give me some time.

1011
01:01:02,822 --> 01:01:04,624
Okay. All right.
Take your time.

1012
01:01:08,345 --> 01:01:09,278
There's your partner.

1013
01:01:09,429 --> 01:01:10,580
I see him.

1014
01:01:10,648 --> 01:01:12,015
Try to move in
on his truck.

1015
01:01:12,182 --> 01:01:13,866
See if we can
get a plate.

1016
01:01:14,785 --> 01:01:16,819
No plate.
Get back on him.

1017
01:01:21,009 --> 01:01:22,475
Stay on him.

1018
01:01:27,332 --> 01:01:28,648
Where's Minuti?

1019
01:01:28,716 --> 01:01:31,051
<i>Federal agent!</i>
<i>Turn the engine off!</i>

1020
01:01:31,119 --> 01:01:33,603
<i>Turn the engine off!</i>

1021
01:01:48,154 --> 01:01:49,988
Tilt back down.

1022
01:01:52,040 --> 01:01:53,875
He's still breathing.

1023
01:02:09,993 --> 01:02:11,727
What can we do?

1024
01:02:11,795 --> 01:02:13,529
I don't know what to do.

1025
01:02:15,966 --> 01:02:19,636
He's traveling east.
He's traveling out of range.

1026
01:02:19,703 --> 01:02:21,638
Okay, what can we do? Anything?
I don't know,

1027
01:02:21,705 --> 01:02:24,323
but if we don't do something
fast, I'm gonna lose this guy.

1028
01:02:24,425 --> 01:02:26,059
We're losing the signal.

1029
01:02:26,177 --> 01:02:27,260
We have to boost the signal.

1030
01:02:27,327 --> 01:02:29,596
We need to chase him
with the goggle rig.

1031
01:02:29,664 --> 01:02:31,431
Yeah, well, Gunnars is
a little busy right now,

1032
01:02:31,498 --> 01:02:33,618
and he's the only one
who can use it.

1033
01:02:35,471 --> 01:02:36,921
Where is it?
What, the rig? It's...

1034
01:02:36,989 --> 01:02:38,656
Yeah, the rig.
Where is it?

1035
01:02:38,724 --> 01:02:40,474
It's in his--
It's in his Hummer.

1036
01:02:43,579 --> 01:02:45,463
Keys in there?
Yeah.

1037
01:03:11,625 --> 01:03:13,727
All right, quiet,
everybody. It's him.

1038
01:03:14,228 --> 01:03:15,328
Carlin.

1039
01:03:15,396 --> 01:03:16,713
Where's he now?

1040
01:03:16,780 --> 01:03:18,198
Is he going east?

1041
01:03:19,984 --> 01:03:21,067
Yes.

1042
01:03:21,135 --> 01:03:23,702
Okay, he's going east,
going up on De Gaulle.

1043
01:03:23,770 --> 01:03:26,990
All right, just try to keep him in
sight, and keep feeding me directions.

1044
01:03:27,057 --> 01:03:29,960
I'll try and track him
with this goggle rig.

1045
01:03:30,078 --> 01:03:30,944
Can he do that?

1046
01:03:31,012 --> 01:03:32,078
Yeah, if he can
catch up to the image

1047
01:03:32,146 --> 01:03:34,765
and keep him in sight,
that could work.

1048
01:03:37,936 --> 01:03:39,687
Hey, how do you
turn this thing on?

1049
01:03:39,754 --> 01:03:42,473
There's an on-off button
on the back of the rig.

1050
01:03:42,624 --> 01:03:44,207
Okay, I see it.

1051
01:03:44,275 --> 01:03:46,494
It's really simple. Wherever you look,
the eyepiece will auto-focus,

1052
01:03:46,562 --> 01:03:48,913
and we'll see what you see.

1053
01:03:52,785 --> 01:03:54,235
Okay, you're live.
You're on.

1054
01:03:54,303 --> 01:03:56,804
<i>Try the goggles.
Hang on, hang on.</i>

1055
01:04:00,893 --> 01:04:02,176
He's gone.
Out of range.

1056
01:04:02,244 --> 01:04:03,377
What?

1057
01:04:03,512 --> 01:04:04,580
Where's he headed?

1058
01:04:04,648 --> 01:04:06,182
<i>He's headed toward the I-10.</i>

1059
01:04:06,250 --> 01:04:08,267
East or west?

1060
01:04:08,335 --> 01:04:10,385
- I don't know.
- I don't know.

1061
01:04:10,453 --> 01:04:12,288
East or west?

1062
01:04:12,355 --> 01:04:14,173
We lost the signal.
We're blind in here.

1063
01:04:14,241 --> 01:04:14,957
<i>I don't know.</i>

1064
01:04:15,108 --> 01:04:16,525
All right, hang on.

1065
01:04:19,312 --> 01:04:21,179
Oh, shit!

1066
01:04:22,700 --> 01:04:25,552
What? What happened?
What happened?

1067
01:04:30,441 --> 01:04:32,792
This is trippy.

1068
01:04:32,860 --> 01:04:33,894
Doug, look straight ahead.

1069
01:04:33,962 --> 01:04:35,545
We've got the window slaved
to your goggles.

1070
01:04:35,613 --> 01:04:38,599
We are seeing what you're
seeing four days in the past.

1071
01:04:40,067 --> 01:04:42,253
Okay, I got him. I got him.
He's back in range.

1072
01:04:42,321 --> 01:04:43,721
He's going west, not east,

1073
01:04:43,789 --> 01:04:45,589
<i>on the Crescent City Bridge.</i>

1074
01:04:48,327 --> 01:04:51,846
There he is.
That's him. Opposite lane.

1075
01:04:51,848 --> 01:04:53,481
I got him.
That's him. That's him.

1076
01:04:53,548 --> 01:04:54,832
I got him!

1077
01:04:56,368 --> 01:04:57,968
Watch the traffic.

1078
01:05:07,080 --> 01:05:08,080
What was that?

1079
01:05:08,148 --> 01:05:09,281
I think he hit something.

1080
01:05:12,552 --> 01:05:16,338
Doug, you've gotta stay with him.
You're gonna lose him again.

1081
01:05:16,406 --> 01:05:17,890
Doug, what's happening?

1082
01:05:22,930 --> 01:05:24,714
I got him! I got him.

1083
01:05:26,299 --> 01:05:27,767
All right,
all right, all right.

1084
01:05:27,835 --> 01:05:30,103
Good.
Now stay with him.

1085
01:05:30,170 --> 01:05:32,905
Send paramedics
to the Crescent City Bridge.

1086
01:05:32,973 --> 01:05:34,441
Got that?

1087
01:05:37,212 --> 01:05:38,445
I lost him.

1088
01:05:47,840 --> 01:05:50,140
- I got him! I got him!
- All right. All right.

1089
01:05:50,208 --> 01:05:51,709
That's him.

1090
01:05:51,760 --> 01:05:53,744
He's headed for
the 10 to the bayou.

1091
01:06:13,684 --> 01:06:16,569
I can see him.
He's right in front of me.

1092
01:06:25,646 --> 01:06:27,146
Carlin!

1093
01:06:27,214 --> 01:06:28,965
What was that?
What the hell was that?

1094
01:06:29,032 --> 01:06:30,550
Doug, are you all right?

1095
01:06:34,088 --> 01:06:35,305
<i>Doug!</i>

1096
01:06:36,290 --> 01:06:37,290
Doug?

1097
01:06:38,960 --> 01:06:41,395
I think it's broken.
I can't see anything.

1098
01:06:41,463 --> 01:06:44,781
We still have a signal here.
You're still transmitting.

1099
01:06:44,849 --> 01:06:46,033
You can see?

1100
01:06:46,101 --> 01:06:47,434
We'll talk you through it.

1101
01:06:47,501 --> 01:06:49,403
Can you still drive?

1102
01:06:49,470 --> 01:06:50,955
Yeah, yeah.
Where is he?

1103
01:06:51,023 --> 01:06:54,342
Give us a 360
with the goggle rig.

1104
01:06:54,410 --> 01:06:57,228
There! There he is!
Pan the thing around.

1105
01:06:57,295 --> 01:06:59,114
Which way?
<i>To your right.</i>

1106
01:06:59,181 --> 01:07:00,598
To your right.

1107
01:07:01,834 --> 01:07:03,635
There! There he is!

1108
01:07:03,703 --> 01:07:05,169
He's taking
the road to the bayou!

1109
01:07:05,237 --> 01:07:06,855
Right there?

1110
01:07:06,923 --> 01:07:08,539
The road is blocked.

1111
01:07:08,608 --> 01:07:10,209
Take the expressway.
It parallels the road.

1112
01:07:10,343 --> 01:07:11,761
Go. Go, go!

1113
01:07:25,608 --> 01:07:26,642
See him?

1114
01:07:26,710 --> 01:07:28,111
Pan right. Pan right!

1115
01:07:28,979 --> 01:07:30,881
You still see him?

1116
01:07:30,948 --> 01:07:32,482
He's at the end
of the bridge.

1117
01:07:32,550 --> 01:07:35,068
You hear me?
He's at the end of the bridge.

1118
01:07:39,890 --> 01:07:41,441
Keep talking to me.

1119
01:07:41,508 --> 01:07:42,425
I don't know what else
to tell you.

1120
01:07:42,493 --> 01:07:44,461
I feel very, very close
to you right now.

1121
01:07:45,396 --> 01:07:47,548
He took the exit
ramp beneath you.

1122
01:07:47,615 --> 01:07:48,949
Take the next off-ramp.

1123
01:07:49,017 --> 01:07:50,901
Take the next off-ramp!

1124
01:07:52,755 --> 01:07:56,006
All right,
I'm on the off-ramp.

1125
01:07:56,074 --> 01:07:57,875
Go right,
then double back on yourself.

1126
01:07:57,943 --> 01:07:59,510
All right, I got it.

1127
01:08:01,814 --> 01:08:04,333
All right,
take another right.

1128
01:08:09,572 --> 01:08:11,890
Still see him?

1129
01:08:11,958 --> 01:08:14,409
He's heading to the bayou.
Take a left here.

1130
01:08:20,500 --> 01:08:22,067
Good, good, good.

1131
01:08:22,134 --> 01:08:24,003
<i>Take it easy, Doug.</i>
<i>He's dead ahead of you.</i>

1132
01:08:24,071 --> 01:08:25,538
Okay, okay, okay.

1133
01:08:32,363 --> 01:08:35,148
He's slowing down, coming to a fence.
Do you see it?

1134
01:08:38,418 --> 01:08:39,953
Yeah, I see it.

1135
01:08:54,753 --> 01:08:56,653
<i>Doug, if you're gonna leave
the Hummer, take the backpack.</i>

1136
01:08:56,721 --> 01:08:58,856
<i>It's the power</i>
<i>source for the rig.</i>

1137
01:09:26,586 --> 01:09:28,337
Can you hear me?
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

1138
01:09:28,404 --> 01:09:30,723
Yeah, we can hear you.
We can hear you.

1139
01:09:30,791 --> 01:09:31,891
All right.

1140
01:09:42,069 --> 01:09:43,820
What's he doing now?

1141
01:09:47,041 --> 01:09:49,510
He's pulled around
the back of the building.

1142
01:09:53,231 --> 01:09:55,183
Looks like a bomb went off.

1143
01:09:55,250 --> 01:09:59,036
Really? We--We see
an intact structure here.

1144
01:09:59,872 --> 01:10:01,322
No damage?

1145
01:10:01,390 --> 01:10:02,890
<i>No, none.</i>

1146
01:10:04,709 --> 01:10:06,911
Looks like
a vehicle's inside.

1147
01:10:06,979 --> 01:10:08,929
An ambulance.
You see that?

1148
01:10:10,132 --> 01:10:11,966
No. Nothing.

1149
01:10:35,642 --> 01:10:37,743
See anything?

1150
01:10:37,811 --> 01:10:39,912
He's dead ahead of you.

1151
01:10:39,981 --> 01:10:41,965
Doug, he's pulling Minuti
out of the car.

1152
01:10:42,032 --> 01:10:43,266
Where?

1153
01:10:43,334 --> 01:10:45,234
All right, now pan to the right.
Pan to the right.

1154
01:10:45,302 --> 01:10:46,570
- More right.
- You got him.

1155
01:10:46,637 --> 01:10:48,387
Yeah, he's dragging
him out of the car.

1156
01:10:48,389 --> 01:10:49,622
Do you see him?

1157
01:10:49,824 --> 01:10:52,243
Yeah.
Yes. Right in front of you.

1158
01:10:52,310 --> 01:10:53,961
Boost the audio for me.

1159
01:10:54,029 --> 01:10:55,830
Audio boosted.

1160
01:10:55,897 --> 01:10:59,299
<i>Turn around.</i>
<i>Turn around behind you.</i>

1161
01:10:59,367 --> 01:11:01,869
Larry?
<i>Pan back to the right.</i>

1162
01:11:01,937 --> 01:11:03,387
You've got him now.
<i>Where is he?</i>

1163
01:11:03,455 --> 01:11:05,456
He's being
dragged on the concrete.

1164
01:11:08,209 --> 01:11:09,444
Larry!

1165
01:11:13,917 --> 01:11:15,600
What's that sound?

1166
01:11:16,519 --> 01:11:18,753
<i>What's the sound?</i>

1167
01:11:18,821 --> 01:11:22,974
He's pouring some kind of
accelerant over Agent Minuti.

1168
01:11:23,042 --> 01:11:26,428
I think it's the diesel fuel,
like at the ferry.

1169
01:11:35,656 --> 01:11:37,256
He's waking up.

1170
01:11:37,258 --> 01:11:40,409
Brace yourselves. I think you're
about to witness a murder.

1171
01:12:53,787 --> 01:12:55,689
If we hadn't sent him there,
he wouldn't be dead now.

1172
01:12:55,756 --> 01:12:58,641
No, he was already dead from the ferry.
We just changed how he died.

1173
01:12:58,709 --> 01:12:59,843
We don't know that.

1174
01:12:59,911 --> 01:13:01,578
He could've been standing
right next to you,

1175
01:13:01,646 --> 01:13:03,064
right until we
sent that note.

1176
01:13:03,131 --> 01:13:04,749
<i>You'd need a branching
multiple universe for that to happen.</i>

1177
01:13:04,816 --> 01:13:07,935
<i>Oh, come on.</i>
<i>We can't change anything.</i>

1178
01:13:07,937 --> 01:13:09,220
We didn't change anything.

1179
01:13:09,287 --> 01:13:11,155
That's what I've been
trying to tell you.

1180
01:13:11,157 --> 01:13:13,740
I'll tell you what we did.

1181
01:13:13,808 --> 01:13:17,144
The suspect used a stolen
Blazer to case the dock.

1182
01:13:17,212 --> 01:13:19,014
So now he has
a truck big enough

1183
01:13:19,082 --> 01:13:21,716
to drive a bomb
onto the ferry.

1184
01:13:21,784 --> 01:13:24,436
<i>Now Larry shows up, right?</i>

1185
01:13:24,504 --> 01:13:27,239
Larry puts bullet holes
through the windshield.

1186
01:13:27,306 --> 01:13:28,406
You want a mask?

1187
01:13:28,474 --> 01:13:29,908
No. No, I'm good, thanks.

1188
01:13:29,976 --> 01:13:32,044
Larry puts bullet holes
through the windshield,

1189
01:13:32,112 --> 01:13:33,445
<i>leaves blood all</i>
<i>over the back seat,</i>

1190
01:13:33,512 --> 01:13:35,480
<i>so now our bomber</i>
<i>needs a new truck,</i>

1191
01:13:35,548 --> 01:13:38,134
you understand?
Claire's truck.

1192
01:13:40,037 --> 01:13:41,421
<i>You hungry?</i>

1193
01:13:41,489 --> 01:13:42,589
Yeah, we changed one thing,

1194
01:13:42,656 --> 01:13:45,291
but by changing one thing,
we didn't change anything.

1195
01:13:45,359 --> 01:13:47,093
<i>What's on TV?</i>

1196
01:14:24,099 --> 01:14:25,517
Hey, hey, hey,
we got a name.

1197
01:14:25,584 --> 01:14:27,702
- Carroll Oerstadt.
- What?

1198
01:14:27,770 --> 01:14:28,687
Who is that?

1199
01:14:28,754 --> 01:14:30,855
Owner of that
bait camp Doug found.

1200
01:14:30,923 --> 01:14:33,860
Truck registration,
airboat registration, match.

1201
01:14:33,927 --> 01:14:35,161
And another property.

1202
01:14:35,229 --> 01:14:38,064
5874 Mullie Ave.,
Ninth Ward, New Orleans.

1203
01:14:38,131 --> 01:14:40,533
Is this a he or a she?
It's a he. Let's go.

1204
01:15:14,569 --> 01:15:15,886
Clear!

1205
01:15:44,150 --> 01:15:47,053
<i>Testing,</i>
<i>one, two, three, four.</i>

1206
01:15:47,120 --> 01:15:51,023
<i>Testing,</i>
<i>one, two, three, four.</i>

1207
01:15:51,091 --> 01:15:55,695
<i>ATF New Orleans, conducting
interview with Carroll Oerstadt.</i>

1208
01:15:55,763 --> 01:15:57,446
<i>You've waived your right</i>
<i>to counsel, right?</i>

1209
01:15:57,514 --> 01:16:00,433
<i>Yes, sir.</i>
<i>Okay.</i>

1210
01:16:00,500 --> 01:16:04,755
<i>I'm fascinated</i>
<i>with your precision.</i>

1211
01:16:04,823 --> 01:16:07,608
It's not very often we see that
level of expertise around here,

1212
01:16:07,675 --> 01:16:10,127
and if it's all right with you,
I'd like to use this interview

1213
01:16:10,195 --> 01:16:13,881
to educate my colleagues
in law enforcement.

1214
01:16:13,948 --> 01:16:15,099
Yes, sir.

1215
01:16:15,167 --> 01:16:17,034
Good. Good.

1216
01:16:17,101 --> 01:16:18,151
Let's talk about motive.

1217
01:16:18,219 --> 01:16:21,874
Why would you use explosives
against the US Navy?

1218
01:16:23,275 --> 01:16:26,177
Correction, sir.
US Government.

1219
01:16:26,245 --> 01:16:28,346
US Government.

1220
01:16:28,414 --> 01:16:31,733
It says here that you tried
to enlist in the Marines.

1221
01:16:31,801 --> 01:16:33,668
You were rejected.
You tried to enlist in the Army,

1222
01:16:33,736 --> 01:16:35,720
you were rejected again.

1223
01:16:35,788 --> 01:16:38,172
Why do you think
they did that?

1224
01:16:39,675 --> 01:16:42,612
Because they
don't want patriots.

1225
01:16:42,680 --> 01:16:46,299
The military no longer recognizes
commitment and purpose.

1226
01:16:46,367 --> 01:16:51,204
They thought I was overcommitted
and psychologically unstable.

1227
01:16:51,271 --> 01:16:53,522
They didn't want to
understand my value.

1228
01:16:53,590 --> 01:16:55,842
They understand it now.

1229
01:16:55,909 --> 01:16:57,877
I believe so. Yes, sir.

1230
01:17:01,499 --> 01:17:03,751
You're ATF, right?
Yes, I am.

1231
01:17:04,786 --> 01:17:06,136
Got a smoke?

1232
01:17:06,203 --> 01:17:07,270
No, I don't.
But I can get you one.

1233
01:17:07,338 --> 01:17:08,922
Would you like one?
Yes.

1234
01:17:08,990 --> 01:17:11,741
Okay. Anything you want to
say, just talk into the mike.

1235
01:17:11,809 --> 01:17:15,045
A man can always use more
alcohol, tobacco and firearms.

1236
01:17:15,113 --> 01:17:17,182
I can think of
one more thing.

1237
01:17:20,936 --> 01:17:23,021
<i>It's like the Revolutionary
War, you know what I mean?</i>

1238
01:17:23,088 --> 01:17:26,891
<i>"One man's terrorist is another
man's patriot," isn't it?</i>

1239
01:17:26,959 --> 01:17:29,060
<i>- Yeah?</i>
<i>- Exactly.</i>

1240
01:17:29,128 --> 01:17:30,745
<i>Yeah.</i>
<i>You get it.</i>

1241
01:17:32,831 --> 01:17:34,549
This wasn't about revenge.

1242
01:17:34,617 --> 01:17:35,884
What was it about?

1243
01:17:38,922 --> 01:17:40,556
Destiny.

1244
01:17:40,624 --> 01:17:41,690
Destiny?

1245
01:17:43,059 --> 01:17:44,576
You've been asking me
about my motives.

1246
01:17:44,645 --> 01:17:46,345
Right. Right.
My methods.

1247
01:17:47,714 --> 01:17:49,799
They're all connected.

1248
01:17:49,866 --> 01:17:51,600
Everything's connected.

1249
01:17:51,667 --> 01:17:53,836
Okay. How was Claire
Kuchever connected?

1250
01:17:53,904 --> 01:17:55,505
I needed a car.

1251
01:17:55,573 --> 01:17:56,989
And that's it?
No, well, something

1252
01:17:57,057 --> 01:17:59,142
that couldn't be traced back to me.
Right.

1253
01:17:59,210 --> 01:18:02,545
I had one ready till
that cop showed up.

1254
01:18:02,613 --> 01:18:05,282
That cop was a federal agent.

1255
01:18:05,349 --> 01:18:07,784
Lawrence Minuti.
My partner. You shot him.

1256
01:18:07,852 --> 01:18:10,804
He... I was about to burn him
and he was waking up, you know?

1257
01:18:10,871 --> 01:18:12,690
I mean, I'm not cruel.

1258
01:18:14,993 --> 01:18:19,463
Well, why didn't you "do that"
for Claire Kuchever?

1259
01:18:20,833 --> 01:18:26,320
Well, because I needed her
to look like a ferry victim,

1260
01:18:26,388 --> 01:18:27,905
and a bullet
would've given it away.

1261
01:18:27,972 --> 01:18:29,190
I see.

1262
01:18:29,258 --> 01:18:32,244
I went to her house on the
pretense of buying her car.

1263
01:18:32,312 --> 01:18:34,095
I took her from behind,
taped her mouth

1264
01:18:34,163 --> 01:18:35,731
and threw
a hood over her head.

1265
01:18:35,798 --> 01:18:36,965
Then?

1266
01:18:37,033 --> 01:18:38,216
<i>I bound her wrists</i>
<i>and her ankles</i>

1267
01:18:38,284 --> 01:18:39,785
<i>and I drove her</i>
<i>back to my place.</i>

1268
01:18:39,853 --> 01:18:41,636
<i>I loaded</i>
<i>the device into her car</i>

1269
01:18:41,704 --> 01:18:43,388
<i>and then I soaked her</i>
<i>with the gasoline.</i>

1270
01:18:43,456 --> 01:18:44,690
Jesus.

1271
01:18:44,757 --> 01:18:45,841
And?

1272
01:18:45,908 --> 01:18:47,476
I think you know
what happened after that.

1273
01:18:47,543 --> 01:18:49,345
No, I don't know. I want you to tell me.
You gotta talk.

1274
01:18:49,413 --> 01:18:51,630
I mean, you know, come on, hero.
What happened after that?

1275
01:18:51,698 --> 01:18:52,798
I'll tell you what
happened after that.

1276
01:18:52,866 --> 01:18:56,302
You killed 543 people.
How do you feel about that?

1277
01:19:01,325 --> 01:19:05,077
I think that you were a murderer
right from the beginning.

1278
01:19:07,548 --> 01:19:11,151
Sometimes a little human
collateral is the cost of freedom.

1279
01:19:11,219 --> 01:19:13,103
To me, those people
were war casualties,

1280
01:19:13,171 --> 01:19:15,206
<i>but to you,</i>
<i>they're just evidence.</i>

1281
01:19:15,273 --> 01:19:17,641
That'll do. We got him.

1282
01:19:17,709 --> 01:19:18,942
<i>What'd you say?</i>

1283
01:19:19,010 --> 01:19:21,162
You think you know
what's coming?

1284
01:19:21,229 --> 01:19:22,879
You don't have a clue.

1285
01:19:22,881 --> 01:19:25,082
I know where you're going.

1286
01:19:25,150 --> 01:19:29,754
I know you're gonna be away
for a long time. I know that.

1287
01:19:29,822 --> 01:19:31,556
This case will
never even go to trial.

1288
01:19:31,623 --> 01:19:32,690
No?

1289
01:19:32,758 --> 01:19:33,791
Uh-uh.

1290
01:19:33,859 --> 01:19:35,060
'Cause I seen what's coming.

1291
01:19:35,127 --> 01:19:36,928
Did... Have you? What?

1292
01:19:37,663 --> 01:19:39,197
What is in this glass?

1293
01:19:39,265 --> 01:19:40,865
You've seen
what's coming, huh?

1294
01:19:40,933 --> 01:19:43,935
Okay, what's coming?
You tell me.

1295
01:19:43,953 --> 01:19:46,705
I told you earlier
I have a destiny,

1296
01:19:46,773 --> 01:19:48,808
a purpose.

1297
01:19:48,875 --> 01:19:52,445
Satan reasons like man,
but God thinks of eternity.

1298
01:19:52,512 --> 01:19:54,630
Well, I prostrate
myself before a world

1299
01:19:54,697 --> 01:19:56,966
that's going to hell
in a handbag,

1300
01:19:57,034 --> 01:20:00,352
'cause in all eternity, I am
here and I will be remembered.

1301
01:20:00,420 --> 01:20:02,571
That's destiny.

1302
01:20:02,639 --> 01:20:04,791
A bomb has a destiny,

1303
01:20:04,859 --> 01:20:07,944
a predetermined fate set by
the hand of its creator.

1304
01:20:08,012 --> 01:20:11,431
And anyone who tries to alter
that destiny will be destroyed.

1305
01:20:11,499 --> 01:20:14,902
Anyone who tries to stop it from
happening will cause it to happen.

1306
01:20:14,969 --> 01:20:17,053
And that's what
you don't understand.

1307
01:20:17,121 --> 01:20:19,272
We're not here to coexist.

1308
01:20:19,340 --> 01:20:21,108
I'm here to win.

1309
01:20:21,175 --> 01:20:24,045
So you'd better have some
divine intervention, buddy.

1310
01:20:24,913 --> 01:20:27,098
You're gonna need it.

1311
01:20:27,165 --> 01:20:29,017
You'd better
have some K-Y.

1312
01:20:29,084 --> 01:20:30,819
You're gonna need it.

1313
01:20:42,715 --> 01:20:44,784
What am I supposed to do?

1314
01:20:46,202 --> 01:20:47,653
We're shutting you down.

1315
01:20:47,804 --> 01:20:48,954
What?

1316
01:20:49,022 --> 01:20:50,222
Yeah, we got what we need.

1317
01:20:50,289 --> 01:20:52,541
The forensics, the suspect,
a confession. We're done.

1318
01:20:52,608 --> 01:20:56,145
Sir, perhaps we should continue
and watch the actual crime.

1319
01:20:56,212 --> 01:20:57,763
The ferry bombing.
Right. He's right.

1320
01:20:57,914 --> 01:21:00,083
I mean, we--we can't just
go on the confession alone.

1321
01:21:00,150 --> 01:21:01,284
We need an airtight case.

1322
01:21:01,352 --> 01:21:02,852
We need to collect
more evidence.

1323
01:21:02,920 --> 01:21:04,804
Well, collecting evidence
would've been fine, Agent Carly.

1324
01:21:04,872 --> 01:21:06,005
You took it
a little further than that.

1325
01:21:06,073 --> 01:21:07,474
Agent Carlin. Carlin.

1326
01:21:07,541 --> 01:21:08,775
My name is Carlin, not Carly.

1327
01:21:08,893 --> 01:21:10,026
We had protocols in place.

1328
01:21:10,094 --> 01:21:11,494
There's strict protocols.

1329
01:21:11,595 --> 01:21:14,230
And then you had to push it,
and now an agent's dead.

1330
01:21:14,298 --> 01:21:16,751
Sir, by one theory,
that already happened.

1331
01:21:16,818 --> 01:21:18,202
We're done.
Power it down.

1332
01:21:18,270 --> 01:21:20,504
Pack it up.
On to the next case.

1333
01:21:20,571 --> 01:21:22,840
What about Claire?
What...

1334
01:21:22,908 --> 01:21:24,859
Lookit, charging Oerstadt
in the Kuchever murder

1335
01:21:24,926 --> 01:21:26,444
is gonna raise
too many questions

1336
01:21:26,511 --> 01:21:27,644
about how we
obtained the evidence.

1337
01:21:27,712 --> 01:21:29,146
I understand that, sir,
but what about Claire?

1338
01:21:29,214 --> 01:21:30,580
Are we just
gonna drop the case?

1339
01:21:30,648 --> 01:21:31,566
We got him on
the ferry bombing,

1340
01:21:31,633 --> 01:21:33,133
we got him on
killing a federal agent.

1341
01:21:33,201 --> 01:21:35,337
That's enough to get him the needle.
I cannot accept that, sir.

1342
01:21:35,405 --> 01:21:38,006
Well, you know, I don't give a
rat's ass what you can accept.

1343
01:21:38,074 --> 01:21:40,609
She doesn't matter.
He's gonna kill her.

1344
01:21:40,677 --> 01:21:42,143
In 12 hours,
he's gonna kill her.

1345
01:21:42,345 --> 01:21:44,329
He killed her four days ago.

1346
01:21:44,331 --> 01:21:47,098
You were at the funeral.
What's wrong with you?

1347
01:21:50,887 --> 01:21:52,420
It had to happen.

1348
01:21:52,488 --> 01:21:56,659
I delayed turning in my report
till we caught the guy.

1349
01:21:56,727 --> 01:21:58,877
Hey, mission accomplished.

1350
01:21:58,945 --> 01:22:00,880
This is a victory, Doug.

1351
01:22:07,888 --> 01:22:11,040
Hey. Now, my job
is closure.

1352
01:22:11,107 --> 01:22:13,677
Your job is to help
facilitate that closure.

1353
01:22:13,745 --> 01:22:16,046
Then you tell me,
what do I tell her father?

1354
01:22:16,113 --> 01:22:18,215
We caught the son of a bitch.

1355
01:22:18,282 --> 01:22:19,516
We can't save the victims.

1356
01:22:19,584 --> 01:22:23,170
It's not our job to make
the relatives feel better.

1357
01:22:23,172 --> 01:22:28,392
We lose everything that we care about.
Those are your words.

1358
01:22:28,460 --> 01:22:31,462
Doug, it's not your fault
that Claire dies.

1359
01:22:33,999 --> 01:22:35,866
Yeah, that's one theory.

1360
01:22:40,389 --> 01:22:43,557
<i>Lieutenant Junior</i>
<i>Grade Dianne Kerry.</i>

1361
01:22:43,625 --> 01:22:45,509
<i>Martin Kyle.</i>

1362
01:22:46,679 --> 01:22:49,848
<i>Commander</i>
<i>Francis Lacey, retired.</i>

1363
01:22:49,916 --> 01:22:52,918
<i>Elaine Lacey.</i>

1364
01:22:52,986 --> 01:22:55,537
<i>Chief Petty Officer</i>
<i>Darren McAndrews.</i>

1365
01:22:56,290 --> 01:22:58,440
<i>Lorraine McAndrews.</i>

1366
01:22:59,843 --> 01:23:03,045
<i>Electronics Technician</i>
<i>Lisa Melville.</i>

1367
01:23:03,113 --> 01:23:05,948
<i>Chaplain Rabbi</i>
<i>Benjamin Mendelsson.</i>

1368
01:24:22,830 --> 01:24:24,732
Denny? It's Doug.

1369
01:24:24,734 --> 01:24:27,968
Well, I can't say
I wasn't expecting this call.

1370
01:24:28,036 --> 01:24:30,604
Look, you know what happens
if you try this.

1371
01:24:30,672 --> 01:24:32,306
We both know
what happens if I don't.

1372
01:24:32,374 --> 01:24:34,942
Well, not a lot of
guinea pigs volunteer

1373
01:24:35,009 --> 01:24:36,743
to die in the name
of science.

1374
01:24:36,811 --> 01:24:38,345
Well, then we have
to make sure

1375
01:24:38,413 --> 01:24:40,715
I end up somewhere
besides the morgue.

1376
01:24:41,350 --> 01:24:42,851
Can you help me?

1377
01:24:47,322 --> 01:24:49,540
I'll see you
when you get here.

1378
01:24:51,110 --> 01:24:52,094
Doug?

1379
01:24:58,218 --> 01:25:03,222
Do me a favor.
When you finish, turn off the lights.

1380
01:25:23,778 --> 01:25:27,381
You do that one more time, you set
off every alarm in the joint.

1381
01:25:31,536 --> 01:25:32,702
Can't take it.

1382
01:25:32,770 --> 01:25:34,438
Gotta keep the mass
as low as possible.

1383
01:25:34,506 --> 01:25:36,558
You gotta take
everything off.

1384
01:25:41,964 --> 01:25:44,415
You can keep
your underwear on.

1385
01:25:44,483 --> 01:25:45,950
Thank you very much.

1386
01:25:45,952 --> 01:25:49,954
Thought you said you didn't
believe in changing the past.

1387
01:25:50,021 --> 01:25:52,690
Right. Well, I also
believe in God.

1388
01:25:52,758 --> 01:25:54,192
Just don't tell anyone.

1389
01:25:54,361 --> 01:25:56,695
I'm gonna tell everybody.
Yeah?

1390
01:25:56,763 --> 01:25:59,331
You know, when I open up the
throttle on this thing...

1391
01:25:59,399 --> 01:26:03,252
Yeah, I know. EM field, flatline.
I got it.

1392
01:26:03,319 --> 01:26:06,088
Thing of it is, no matter
how clever we think we are,

1393
01:26:06,156 --> 01:26:08,758
the most probable outcome
of our little experiment

1394
01:26:08,825 --> 01:26:10,025
is that four
and a half days ago

1395
01:26:10,093 --> 01:26:12,595
you get a call from
the coroner's office.

1396
01:26:12,663 --> 01:26:14,865
"Hey, Agent Carlin,
I want you to come down here.

1397
01:26:14,932 --> 01:26:16,816
"There's something
you should see."

1398
01:26:16,883 --> 01:26:19,802
And next thing you know,
you're standing over a corpse

1399
01:26:19,870 --> 01:26:21,704
and it's you.

1400
01:26:21,772 --> 01:26:27,126
Well, you can be wrong a million times.
You only gotta be right once.

1401
01:26:27,194 --> 01:26:29,479
Besides, I think I'd remember
if that happened, right?

1402
01:26:29,546 --> 01:26:31,849
So I gotta face out
toward you?

1403
01:26:31,917 --> 01:26:34,551
Yeah, face out.
Just like the note, only bigger.

1404
01:26:36,004 --> 01:26:37,455
You ready?

1405
01:26:37,523 --> 01:26:38,489
No.

1406
01:26:39,508 --> 01:26:41,775
You don't have to do this.

1407
01:26:43,528 --> 01:26:45,512
What if I already have?

1408
01:26:46,114 --> 01:26:47,365
Right.

1409
01:27:00,680 --> 01:27:01,780
Doug?

1410
01:27:03,783 --> 01:27:04,983
<i>Doug?</i>

1411
01:27:05,051 --> 01:27:07,904
Hey. Hello?

1412
01:27:07,972 --> 01:27:10,023
You okay in there?
<i>Yeah.</i>

1413
01:27:10,090 --> 01:27:11,841
You good?
Yeah, yeah, I'm good.

1414
01:27:11,909 --> 01:27:14,676
I'm beside myself.

1415
01:27:17,431 --> 01:27:19,032
<i>Am I still here?</i>

1416
01:27:19,099 --> 01:27:20,466
For now. You ready?

1417
01:27:20,533 --> 01:27:22,235
<i>Yeah, I'm ready.</i>
<i>All right.</i>

1418
01:27:22,402 --> 01:27:24,203
<i>Looking forward to walking
up to you four days ago</i>

1419
01:27:24,271 --> 01:27:25,489
<i>and blowing</i>
<i>your mind, though.</i>

1420
01:27:25,556 --> 01:27:26,874
Well, if that happens,
maybe you can tell me

1421
01:27:26,941 --> 01:27:28,341
what it's like to
meet your younger self.

1422
01:27:28,409 --> 01:27:30,511
<i>All right,</i>
<i>I'll let you know.</i>

1423
01:27:30,513 --> 01:27:32,496
All right, remember,
the ferry blows

1424
01:27:32,563 --> 01:27:35,282
at 10:50 on Fat Tuesday,
okay?

1425
01:27:36,083 --> 01:27:37,100
<i>Yeah.</i>

1426
01:27:38,369 --> 01:27:39,670
Here we go.

1427
01:27:40,955 --> 01:27:42,072
See you yesterday.

1428
01:27:42,140 --> 01:27:43,590
God willing.

1429
01:28:08,302 --> 01:28:09,735
<i>Good, good.</i>

1430
01:28:09,802 --> 01:28:10,852
<i>- You don't have to do this.</i>
<i>- Hello?</i>

1431
01:28:10,920 --> 01:28:12,320
<i>Maybe I already have.</i>

1432
01:28:12,388 --> 01:28:13,739
<i>Maybe I already have.</i>

1433
01:28:16,776 --> 01:28:18,544
- What the hell?
- All right, hold on, everybody.

1434
01:28:18,612 --> 01:28:21,732
The reserve generators
should kick in. Nobody move.

1435
01:28:21,799 --> 01:28:23,650
That was interesting.

1436
01:28:27,204 --> 01:28:28,805
Doctor!
Who the hell is that?

1437
01:28:28,873 --> 01:28:31,975
Where'd he come from?

1438
01:28:32,043 --> 01:28:35,511
All right, let's get him into Trauma.
Trauma 2, Trauma 2!

1439
01:28:40,768 --> 01:28:42,303
This is weird.

1440
01:28:44,155 --> 01:28:46,173
Defib.
Clear!

1441
01:28:46,241 --> 01:28:48,075
Recharge it again.

1442
01:28:48,694 --> 01:28:50,594
Clear!

1443
01:28:50,662 --> 01:28:52,563
Recharge to 300.
Charging.

1444
01:28:52,731 --> 01:28:53,965
Clear!

1445
01:28:55,650 --> 01:29:00,356
Resume CPR. One, two, three, four,
five, six, seven, eight.

1446
01:29:26,500 --> 01:29:28,117
<i>...thirty-four degrees.</i>

1447
01:29:28,185 --> 01:29:30,603
<i>Forty-nine was our low
temperature at the airport.</i>

1448
01:29:30,671 --> 01:29:34,073
<i>Gonna be at that or just maybe
above that for tonight.</i>

1449
01:29:34,141 --> 01:29:35,258
<i>Let me show you why.</i>

1450
01:29:35,326 --> 01:29:36,843
<i>Look,</i>
<i>the winds are starting...</i>

1451
01:29:55,715 --> 01:29:57,449
...a few of them
come back.

1452
01:29:57,516 --> 01:29:59,717
I'm thinking about
getting a tattoo.

1453
01:30:00,720 --> 01:30:01,920
Whoa!
I'm a federal agent.

1454
01:30:01,922 --> 01:30:04,155
I need your keys.
I need a vehicle.

1455
01:30:04,223 --> 01:30:06,107
There's keys
in the truck there.

1456
01:30:06,175 --> 01:30:08,259
Which one? Right here?
Put your hands down.

1457
01:30:08,327 --> 01:30:11,446
Hands on the table.
Hold your donut. Hands right there.

1458
01:30:13,366 --> 01:30:14,384
Water it.

1459
01:30:36,391 --> 01:30:39,259
<i>This might be a
metaphor for existence itself.</i>

1460
01:30:39,326 --> 01:30:41,795
<i>A fish</i>
<i>struggles instinctively</i>

1461
01:30:41,863 --> 01:30:44,814
<i>against an almost</i>
<i>formless antagonist.</i>

1462
01:30:44,882 --> 01:30:46,883
<i>The fish is</i>
<i>a largemouth bass.</i>

1463
01:31:01,233 --> 01:31:03,467
<i>Here's the news at 8:30.</i>

1464
01:31:03,535 --> 01:31:06,354
<i>Federal officials are still
baffled by the massive blackout</i>

1465
01:31:06,421 --> 01:31:08,273
<i>that darkened</i>
<i>the entire eastern half</i>

1466
01:31:08,341 --> 01:31:10,342
<i>of the country</i>
<i>early this morning.</i>

1467
01:33:05,430 --> 01:33:06,664
Hey!

1468
01:34:28,534 --> 01:34:30,186
Jesus.

1469
01:34:36,310 --> 01:34:39,245
Wait a minute.
Hey, it's okay. Wait a minute!

1470
01:34:39,313 --> 01:34:41,163
Listen. Claire!

1471
01:34:41,231 --> 01:34:45,034
I'm a federal agent.
Hang on, hang on.

1472
01:34:45,102 --> 01:34:46,569
All right, it's okay.
It's okay. It's okay.

1473
01:34:46,637 --> 01:34:49,239
I'm a federal agent.
It's okay. It's okay.

1474
01:34:50,508 --> 01:34:52,209
You're safe.
You're all right, okay?

1475
01:34:52,277 --> 01:34:54,361
I'm a federal agent.
You're safe.

1476
01:34:54,429 --> 01:34:56,463
You're safe.
Look at me. Come here.

1477
01:34:56,530 --> 01:34:59,015
You're safe.
He's gone. All right?

1478
01:35:01,269 --> 01:35:02,470
Get me out of here!

1479
01:35:02,537 --> 01:35:03,704
All right. All right.

1480
01:35:03,771 --> 01:35:05,906
Get me out of here!

1481
01:35:05,974 --> 01:35:09,528
It's all right.
It's okay. It's okay.

1482
01:35:11,097 --> 01:35:12,263
Get me out of here.

1483
01:35:12,331 --> 01:35:13,831
All right,
let me get your feet.

1484
01:35:13,899 --> 01:35:16,718
It's all right. It's all right.
It's all right.

1485
01:35:19,405 --> 01:35:21,889
Hey, look at me.
Look at me.

1486
01:35:21,958 --> 01:35:24,576
I'm gonna get you
out of here, okay?

1487
01:35:24,644 --> 01:35:26,161
All right.

1488
01:35:40,561 --> 01:35:43,597
How'd you know there'd
be keys in this truck?

1489
01:35:43,665 --> 01:35:46,416
That's a good question.
I didn't know.

1490
01:35:49,837 --> 01:35:51,955
He's a terrorist?
Yeah.

1491
01:35:52,023 --> 01:35:54,474
His name is
Carroll Oerstadt.

1492
01:35:54,542 --> 01:35:56,543
I'm a part of a special
surveillance unit.

1493
01:35:56,611 --> 01:35:58,228
We've been tracking him.

1494
01:35:58,295 --> 01:36:02,599
He's planning on blowing up the
Canal Street Ferry today at 10:50.

1495
01:36:06,038 --> 01:36:07,405
So we're going
to the police?

1496
01:36:07,472 --> 01:36:09,190
No, it's too complicated.

1497
01:36:09,258 --> 01:36:11,125
By the time we get them up to
speed, the ferry will be gone.

1498
01:36:11,193 --> 01:36:12,894
We gotta go straight
to the Algiers dock.

1499
01:36:12,961 --> 01:36:14,161
I don't think
you're gonna make it.

1500
01:36:14,229 --> 01:36:15,764
You're losing
too much blood.

1501
01:36:15,798 --> 01:36:17,499
No, I gotta make it.
I only got an hour and 40 minutes

1502
01:36:17,566 --> 01:36:18,983
to catch up to this guy.

1503
01:36:19,051 --> 01:36:22,521
What if you don't make it?
What happens then?

1504
01:36:22,588 --> 01:36:24,540
If I don't make it...

1505
01:36:26,476 --> 01:36:27,943
What?

1506
01:36:29,011 --> 01:36:30,212
Your house is on the way.

1507
01:36:30,280 --> 01:36:31,880
We'll go by your house,
and I'll get cleaned up.

1508
01:36:32,082 --> 01:36:33,999
I'll drop you off.
All right?

1509
01:36:34,067 --> 01:36:35,901
All right.

1510
01:36:36,836 --> 01:36:38,421
Hey, Ginger.

1511
01:36:39,189 --> 01:36:41,107
She hates strangers.

1512
01:36:41,175 --> 01:36:42,575
You need anything?

1513
01:36:42,643 --> 01:36:44,544
You get cleaned up.
I'll take care of this.

1514
01:36:44,611 --> 01:36:45,996
You sure?
I could bind that for you.

1515
01:36:46,063 --> 01:36:48,114
No, I'm sure.
You go ahead.

1516
01:36:48,181 --> 01:36:50,550
I'm gonna need to borrow one of
your boyfriend's jackets, though.

1517
01:36:50,617 --> 01:36:51,885
Sure.

1518
01:37:39,069 --> 01:37:41,253
Hey, uh, listen.

1519
01:37:41,321 --> 01:37:42,605
You shouldn't wear that.

1520
01:37:42,673 --> 01:37:44,673
What?

1521
01:37:44,741 --> 01:37:46,142
Why don't you put on
a different one?

1522
01:37:46,210 --> 01:37:49,445
The blue and white one.
Anything. It's just...

1523
01:37:49,512 --> 01:37:51,080
Just trust me.

1524
01:37:51,148 --> 01:37:54,802
The victim wore a dress like
that and it wouldn't be good.

1525
01:37:56,320 --> 01:37:58,655
Okay.
Trust me.

1526
01:37:58,723 --> 01:38:03,076
All right, uh, I--I'll go change.
I'll be right out.

1527
01:38:13,489 --> 01:38:15,423
Stop right there!
Don't move!

1528
01:38:15,490 --> 01:38:17,642
Don't move.
I'm calling the police.

1529
01:38:17,709 --> 01:38:19,360
I am the police.
No, you're not.

1530
01:38:19,428 --> 01:38:21,095
Yes, I am.
No, you're not!

1531
01:38:21,163 --> 01:38:22,180
You didn't ask me
any questions.

1532
01:38:22,247 --> 01:38:23,715
You didn't take
a statement.

1533
01:38:23,783 --> 01:38:27,468
And you knew where my house
was, what's in my closet.

1534
01:38:27,536 --> 01:38:29,020
Who are you?

1535
01:38:29,088 --> 01:38:31,440
I'm Doug Carlin.
I'm an ATF agent.

1536
01:38:31,508 --> 01:38:34,243
I'm part of a special surveillance
unit that's been tracking the man

1537
01:38:34,310 --> 01:38:36,078
who was trying to kill you.
How do I know that?

1538
01:38:36,145 --> 01:38:37,846
I had a hood over my head.
You could be him.

1539
01:38:37,914 --> 01:38:38,998
Just think about it, Claire.

1540
01:38:39,065 --> 01:38:40,699
Look at my face.
You scratched the man's face.

1541
01:38:40,767 --> 01:38:42,451
Do I have a scratch
on my face?

1542
01:38:42,519 --> 01:38:44,637
You scratched him,
didn't you?

1543
01:38:44,704 --> 01:38:46,471
Get on the floor.

1544
01:38:47,573 --> 01:38:49,392
Now! Get on the floor!

1545
01:38:52,380 --> 01:38:53,931
All the way!

1546
01:38:57,151 --> 01:38:59,285
ATF New Orleans,
Agent Donnelly.

1547
01:38:59,353 --> 01:39:03,556
Yes, is there an Agent Douglas
Carlin working out of that branch?

1548
01:39:03,624 --> 01:39:06,527
<i>Yes, there is,</i>
<i>but he's not here right now.</i>

1549
01:39:06,595 --> 01:39:08,445
Would you like to
leave a message?

1550
01:39:08,513 --> 01:39:10,464
Can you describe
him for me, please?

1551
01:39:10,532 --> 01:39:13,033
How tall, skin color.

1552
01:39:13,101 --> 01:39:18,105
I don't know. He's 6'3",
black, not bad-looking.

1553
01:39:20,842 --> 01:39:23,410
Okay, have him call me back

1554
01:39:23,478 --> 01:39:26,999
at 877-504-8423.

1555
01:39:27,066 --> 01:39:28,800
Okay, wait.
My phone pad's empty.

1556
01:39:28,868 --> 01:39:30,152
All right, got it.

1557
01:39:31,954 --> 01:39:32,821
Hello?

1558
01:39:37,977 --> 01:39:39,294
Get up.

1559
01:39:46,537 --> 01:39:48,654
Are you gonna
tell me the truth?

1560
01:39:48,722 --> 01:39:52,007
Are you gonna tell me why you're
here, why this is happening

1561
01:39:52,026 --> 01:39:54,777
and none of it makes sense?
None of it.

1562
01:39:56,430 --> 01:39:57,797
What if you had
to tell someone

1563
01:39:57,865 --> 01:39:59,165
the most important
thing in the world,

1564
01:39:59,233 --> 01:40:01,568
but you knew they'd
never believe you?

1565
01:40:03,538 --> 01:40:04,721
What would you do?

1566
01:40:05,791 --> 01:40:07,958
I'd try.

1567
01:40:08,025 --> 01:40:10,728
You never know
what someone might believe.

1568
01:40:17,051 --> 01:40:21,522
I don't understand what's...
What's happening.

1569
01:40:45,932 --> 01:40:47,767
I gotta hurry up
and get down there.

1570
01:40:47,834 --> 01:40:50,669
Why are you the only one
who can stop him?

1571
01:40:50,737 --> 01:40:52,822
Well, because I'm the only
one that knows his plan.

1572
01:40:52,890 --> 01:40:54,423
I'm the only one that knows
where he's gonna be

1573
01:40:54,490 --> 01:40:56,158
and exactly
what he's gonna do.

1574
01:40:56,226 --> 01:40:57,861
How do you know that?

1575
01:40:57,929 --> 01:41:00,764
I mean, how'd you know
those things about me?

1576
01:41:00,832 --> 01:41:02,599
Well,
for the sake of argument,

1577
01:41:02,666 --> 01:41:05,269
let's just say that the
government has a special device

1578
01:41:05,286 --> 01:41:09,523
that allows me to know what's
gonna happen ahead of time.

1579
01:41:09,591 --> 01:41:11,975
Then how come you didn't know I
was gonna pull a gun on you?

1580
01:41:12,043 --> 01:41:14,611
I did. No, I didn't.

1581
01:41:18,300 --> 01:41:20,418
Is that okay?
Yeah, it's good.

1582
01:41:21,837 --> 01:41:23,404
One second.

1583
01:41:27,960 --> 01:41:31,111
I think that's gonna stay.
Is that okay?

1584
01:41:31,180 --> 01:41:32,480
Yeah, it's great.

1585
01:41:32,548 --> 01:41:33,330
Okay.

1586
01:41:35,551 --> 01:41:37,386
All right.
I'm not very good at this.

1587
01:41:37,453 --> 01:41:39,121
You're very good.

1588
01:41:52,620 --> 01:41:54,437
What's the matter?

1589
01:41:55,439 --> 01:41:56,956
Jesus.

1590
01:42:00,244 --> 01:42:03,413
I haven't changed a thing.

1591
01:42:03,480 --> 01:42:05,748
I gotta go.
And you gotta go with me. Come on.

1592
01:42:05,816 --> 01:42:07,483
What?

1593
01:42:07,551 --> 01:42:08,784
I thought you said
I was safe now.

1594
01:42:08,853 --> 01:42:10,053
I was wrong.
I was wrong.

1595
01:42:10,120 --> 01:42:12,089
You gotta go with me now.
Right now.

1596
01:42:13,091 --> 01:42:15,292
Wait, wait, wait!
Don't answer it.

1597
01:42:17,629 --> 01:42:18,896
Don't answer it.
I'll prove it to you.

1598
01:42:18,964 --> 01:42:20,097
That's your friend
Beth calling.

1599
01:42:20,165 --> 01:42:21,998
Let the machine pick it up.
She's gonna say,

1600
01:42:22,066 --> 01:42:23,551
<i>"Hi, Claire.
It's Beth. Are you there?</i>

1601
01:42:23,618 --> 01:42:25,336
"I'm sorry to
call you so early,

1602
01:42:25,403 --> 01:42:28,906
"but when you didn't call me
last night I got worried."

1603
01:42:28,975 --> 01:42:31,760
<i>Claire? Hi, it's Beth.</i>
<i>Are you there?</i>

1604
01:42:31,827 --> 01:42:33,412
<i>I'm sorry to</i>
<i>call you so early,</i>

1605
01:42:33,479 --> 01:42:35,297
<i>but you said you were gonna
call me when you got home,</i>

1606
01:42:35,365 --> 01:42:37,432
<i>and when you didn't,</i>
<i>I started to get worried.</i>

1607
01:42:37,500 --> 01:42:39,167
Beth, is this a joke?
<i>Oh, hey, hey! No.</i>

1608
01:42:39,234 --> 01:42:40,918
<i>Like--Like I said, I was just
worried about you, that's all.</i>

1609
01:42:40,986 --> 01:42:43,238
I can't talk right now.
Someone's here. I'll call you later.

1610
01:42:43,305 --> 01:42:44,606
<i>Claire...</i>

1611
01:42:44,674 --> 01:42:47,476
Believe me, the only one you're
gonna be safe with is me.

1612
01:42:47,544 --> 01:42:49,445
Okay.
Let's go.

1613
01:42:54,368 --> 01:42:56,001
I don't understand.

1614
01:42:56,069 --> 01:42:59,938
Why not just call the police and
have them arrest him at the dock?

1615
01:43:00,006 --> 01:43:02,091
He'll set the bomb off
right there on the spot.

1616
01:43:02,159 --> 01:43:03,726
He can't know
he's been compromised

1617
01:43:03,794 --> 01:43:05,896
until it's too late for him
to do anything about it.

1618
01:43:05,964 --> 01:43:08,832
He'll set the timer, walk away
on foot, get on his motorcycle

1619
01:43:08,900 --> 01:43:11,669
and ride to the Crescent
City Bridge to watch.

1620
01:43:11,671 --> 01:43:13,837
Okay, then what?

1621
01:43:13,905 --> 01:43:15,723
You defuse the bomb?

1622
01:43:15,790 --> 01:43:17,958
Then I defuse the bomb.

1623
01:44:16,103 --> 01:44:17,971
There's my truck.

1624
01:44:27,583 --> 01:44:29,583
All these people.
There he is.

1625
01:44:29,651 --> 01:44:31,169
Where?

1626
01:44:31,236 --> 01:44:34,355
You see the military jacket
coming this way?

1627
01:44:38,194 --> 01:44:39,929
It's just what you said.

1628
01:44:39,996 --> 01:44:43,265
All right, you see those
officers behind you?

1629
01:44:43,333 --> 01:44:45,567
Yeah.
When the ferry pulls off,

1630
01:44:45,635 --> 01:44:48,086
I want you to tell them
about the bomb, all right?

1631
01:44:48,154 --> 01:44:50,539
They'll believe me?
They better believe you.

1632
01:44:50,607 --> 01:44:51,956
Come on,
they'll arrest me.

1633
01:44:52,024 --> 01:44:52,874
They won't arrest you.

1634
01:44:52,942 --> 01:44:54,326
They'll take you
into custody.

1635
01:44:54,394 --> 01:44:56,929
You'll be fine.
That's a good thing.

1636
01:44:56,997 --> 01:44:58,481
Don't turn around.

1637
01:45:05,038 --> 01:45:06,272
Doug...

1638
01:45:09,309 --> 01:45:10,710
Be careful.

1639
01:45:43,663 --> 01:45:45,530
<i>Your attention, please.</i>

1640
01:45:45,598 --> 01:45:48,083
<i>Passengers are not allowed</i>
<i>on the car deck</i>

1641
01:45:48,150 --> 01:45:50,902
<i>when the ferry is in motion.</i>

1642
01:45:57,711 --> 01:45:59,078
Sir! Sir.

1643
01:45:59,146 --> 01:46:01,864
Excuse me, sir, you're gonna
have to move to the upper deck.

1644
01:46:01,866 --> 01:46:02,932
Passengers
aren't allowed here.

1645
01:46:03,000 --> 01:46:04,350
Okay.

1646
01:46:43,843 --> 01:46:46,043
Can't believe it.
They're right on time.

1647
01:46:46,111 --> 01:46:48,397
Let's get these boys
to their party.

1648
01:47:11,054 --> 01:47:13,022
Mama!

1649
01:48:55,414 --> 01:48:57,666
Excuse me, sir? Sir!

1650
01:48:57,734 --> 01:49:01,270
There's no passengers allowed
on the car deck during transit.

1651
01:49:04,390 --> 01:49:06,708
No passengers allowed, sir.

1652
01:49:21,209 --> 01:49:22,275
Let's go! Let's go!

1653
01:50:20,003 --> 01:50:22,739
It's destiny, Oerstadt.

1654
01:50:22,807 --> 01:50:25,775
Satan reasons like a man,
but God thinks of eternity.

1655
01:50:28,497 --> 01:50:30,280
What did you say?

1656
01:50:30,348 --> 01:50:33,667
I'm saying it's gonna take a little
divine intervention here, buddy.

1657
01:50:35,787 --> 01:50:37,471
I'm coming out.

1658
01:50:45,480 --> 01:50:47,331
What'd you say?

1659
01:50:48,217 --> 01:50:50,068
I thought you were a patriot.

1660
01:50:50,136 --> 01:50:51,486
Oh, I am.

1661
01:50:52,554 --> 01:50:55,306
Patriotism
requires sacrifice.

1662
01:50:55,374 --> 01:50:57,109
I'm willing to sacrifice.

1663
01:50:57,176 --> 01:50:58,676
Yeah? Who? Her? Me?

1664
01:50:58,744 --> 01:51:01,546
You're willing to sacrifice
others, but not yourself.

1665
01:51:01,613 --> 01:51:03,465
The Tree of Liberty
must be refreshed

1666
01:51:03,533 --> 01:51:05,902
with the blood of
patriots and tyrants.

1667
01:51:07,171 --> 01:51:08,204
Right.

1668
01:51:08,271 --> 01:51:09,539
Sometimes
a little human collateral

1669
01:51:09,606 --> 01:51:12,074
is the cost of freedom,
isn't it?

1670
01:51:17,014 --> 01:51:18,915
Who are you, Oerstadt?

1671
01:51:22,152 --> 01:51:23,436
Who are you?

